How about when there's already two of them on a raid? Sort of like trying to be the second cleric in an XP group at that point ... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukevankraveskoins.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kevan Kraveskoins</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/10/02 7:00:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2318.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> Uh.. some of you may know me, some don't.  But I felt like chiming in.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I played a 60 chanter on Tribunal for well over a year ( gave him away when I quit in the summer of last year, and started a new account on Vaz as a rogue which is currently 52 or 53.  I don't know the exact level nowadays, have to ask Joeb if he level'd him any <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) and I have to disagree with Herder saying they die first.  <br>
<br>
Don't take this the wrong way, it's not insulting to your skills, but.. if you're dying first then you're not doing something right.  I very rarely had anyone die in evac/raid situations, unless it was such a bad pull that people were dying within seconds.  In that instance it really doesn't matter a bit who dies first because the time between each death isn't very long.<br>
<br>
You might want to ask a few other enchanters around you some tactics in keeping people alive during an evac.  Before the tash series agro was changed during SoV, it was quite easy to land an AE tash on a group of mobs agro'd on a healer during an evac, and a good cleric would recognize the enchanter is about to get pounded and dump heals on them.  Obviously that's not possible anymore, but there's still ways around it.  You COULD substitute that AE tash nowadays with a stun but you'd have to make sure you hit your wide area stun, of course.  <br>
<br>
If you know when the evac is cast ( evac messages in groupsay from the caster helps ), you can run quite a distance from the group with the mobs, and then run them back in the other direction as the evac is about to hit.  You save quite a lot of damage if you time it right.  In an area where you have a zoneline that you can run to, have a hotkey set to say in capitals &quot;RUN TO THE ZONE NOW OR DIE!&quot; and spam it 2 or 3 times as you hit a long duration stun.  If they don't move, sucks to be them, you gave them at least 6 seconds worth of time to get a hell of a head start, that must be even easier nowadays with Run 3.  They'll have nobody to blame but themselves if they die.  <br>
<br>
Again, it's not that I'm bashing your skills, but maybe open yourself up to some new, unorthodox tactics and you might be surprised that things are made a lot easier on yourself in certain situations.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If anyone has a 60 enchanter they don't play, and someone needs one, just send me the password/login.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I agree that they're boring in raid situations, but I didn't play one in SoL situations so hopefully that changed.  It was the primary reason I quit playing him.<br>
